<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12">
      <h3><center>About Indy Public Transit Survey</center></h3>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row other-info">
    <div class="col-sm-3 col-md-3 col-lg-3">
      <h4>The Survey</h4>
        <%= image_tag('survey_map.png', width: "40%", class: "img-responsive", alt: "Responsive Image", class: "img-rounded") %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-8 col-md-8 col-lg-8">
      <p>Why this app exists</p>
      <p>What this app is used for</p>
      <p>Who would benefit from using this app</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-1 col-md-1 col-lg-1">
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr>
  <div class="row app-bio">
    <div class="col-sm-3 col-md-3 col-lg-3">
      <h4>How to use this app</h4>
      <%= image_tag('heatmap_image2.png', width: "40%", class: "img-responsive", alt: "Responsive Image", class: "img-rounded") %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-8 col-md-8 col-lg-8">
      <h5>For the commuter:</h5>
      <p>Origin/Destination address</p>
      <h5>How to read the heatmap</h5>
      <p>Look at it.</p>
      <h5>For the decision makers:</h5>
      <p>How to generate results for communities</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-1 col-md-1 col-lg-1">
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr>
  <div class="row author-bio">
    <div class="col-sm-3 col-md-3 col-lg-3">
      <h4>About the Developer</h4>
      <%= image_tag('marie_720.jpg', width: "40%", class: "img-responsive", alt: "Responsive Image", class: "img-rounded") %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-8 col-md-8 col-lg-8">
      <p>Hello! My name is Marie Denney and I am passionate about improving and bringing more public transportation options to Indianapolis, most specifically, a light rail system that would connect the suburbs to the heart of Indianapolis. I currently live in one of the steadily growing suburbs of Indianapolis and would glady use public transportation to get around, if it was made available to me. In my travels, I use public transportation whenever it is available, my favorite means being light rail and commuter rail systems. Both provide me with a way to enjoy my surroundings without having to worry about traffic and the cost of a rental car.</p>
      <p>I recently completed a 12-week immersive Back End Engineering development program focusing on Ruby on Rails at The Iron Yard, Indianapolis Campus. For my final project, I expressed a desire to collect, analyze and disseminate commuter data for commuters in the Indianapolis area. As such, I created the Indy Public Transit Survey as a way to collect and disseminate data regarding the routes most frequently traveled by commuters.</p>
      <p><%= link_to "Contact Me", 'contact', class: "btn btn-default btn-small" %></p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-1 col-md-1 col-lg-1">
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr>
  <div class="row dev-used">
    <div class="col-sm-3 col-md-3 col-lg-3">
      <h4>Development Tools</h4>
        <%= image_tag('Ruby_on_Rails-logo.png', width: "30%", class: "img-responsive", alt: "Responsive Image", class: "img-rounded") %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-8 col-md-8 col-lg-8">
      <p>Rails combines the Ruby programming language with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to create a web application that runs on a web server.</p>
